Chris Lu, Assistant to the President and Cabinet Secretary, is leaving the White House. President Obama praised Lu for his long and dedicated service, including crafting legislative agendas and managing relations with the Cabinet. Lu has overseen a stable and effective Cabinet that has achieved significant accomplishments over the past four years. The President has asked Lu to consider other opportunities to serve in his administration after taking some time off. The entire Cabinet expressed gratitude for Lu's friendship and exceptional service to the nation.